==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pyroscope
<hw>Pyr"o*scope</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Pyro-</ets>
+ <ets>-scope</ets>: cf. F. <ets>pyroscope</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>An instrument for measuring the intensity of
heat radiating from a fire, or the cooling influence of bodies. It is a
differential thermometer, having one bulb coated with gold or silver
leaf.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

